  "VERDICT": {
    "verdict": "refuted (as a tradeable neutral L/S signal); confirms audit",
    "a_momentum": "IS momentum/sector disguise. Long leg 95% tech_score==1.0; long-leg 20d-momentum exceeds short-leg EVERY day by avg +27pp. The free-momentum tilt is structural. Raw-momentum tercile L/S earns NEGATIVE only because combined adds a hardware-long/software-short SECTOR overlay (D2: long 56 hw/2 sw, short 36 sw/22 hw) on top of the momentum tilt. A2 residual-survival is an artifact of a weak 13-name single-factor control inside a momentum-clustered tercile, not independent alpha.",
    "b_single_day_name": "Driven by single names/days. f5 LS sum +57.96 of which MRVL alone = +48.12 (83%); top-3 names >100%. Leave-one-name MRVL drops f5 from +0.79 to +0.31 (long-leg only). f1/f2/f3 flip sign on leave-one-day (2026-06-01) and leave-one-name (MRVL/ORCL). Only f5 has 0 sign-flips, but that is because the SAME concentrated long winners dominate.",
    "c_effective_n": "Effective N tiny. f5 non-overlap n=3, calendar/hold=3.6. Naive t=1.48 deflates to 0.66 after overlap correction; block-bootstrap 2-sided p=0.086 (f5 best), 0.74/0.96/0.95 (f1/f2/f3). All 95% CIs straddle 0. No statistical power. Matches audit perm-p f5=0.156.",
    "d_survivorship": "Tradability/sector bias confirmed. The 30 perp-mappable names ARE a hardware-vs-software split; the win is a sector bet. Ticker-bootstrap f5 frac-positive 0.91 but that just resamples the SAME MRVL-heavy universe; p05 dips to -0.19. Conclusion would not survive a different/larger universe and is not a name-agnostic signal.",
    "e_cost_stress": "At 0.20%/leg: f1 0.47->0.27, f3 0.05->-0.02 (flips neg), f2 stays neg; only f5 survives nominally (0.788->0.748) but f5 IS the MRVL-driven, statistically-insignificant horizon. Cost erodes the already-marginal short horizons; the surviving one is the unreliable one."
